main event: Three unidentified objects were sighted over Xenia, Ohio on March 27, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as bright white in a bluish color, making a loud buzzing sound.
The objects were reportedly the size of a small head and moved faster than a jet aircraft.
The objects were observed by a wide family grouping, including several generations of the same family.
The objects performed various maneuvers such as stopping, making right-angle turns, and disappearing behind trees.
The Air Force requested that the witness family members fill out additional reporting forms for further investigation.
witnesses: a wide family grouping (3 generations of sisters)
